    <h1>Symbolic Logic</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Oscar Levin &middot; CC BY-SA 4.0 &middot; <a href="https://discrete.openmathbooks.org/">Discrete Mathematics: An Open Introduction, Ch. 3</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Logic is the grammar of proof. Propositions are sentences that are true or false. Connectives combine them. Quantifiers range over domains. <strong>Logical equivalence</strong> lets you rewrite statements without changing their truth, which is the entire engine of formal proof.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: Truth table for implication -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
